<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-11-29T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-11-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="390" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d390">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">Tehran Legation Files</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Iran</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_DLGJ1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Dreyfus</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the President’s
                                    Special Representative</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_HPJ1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Hurley</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#left"><hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi></seg>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Tehran</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-11-29">November 29, 1943</date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear General <persName corresp="#p_HPJ1">Hurley</persName></hi>: This morning the Prime Minister, M.
                                Soheily, told me he had seen Mr. <persName corresp="#p_EA1">Eden</persName> today and had taken up with <pb facs="0724" n="620" xml:id="pg_620"/> him the possibility of the issuance,
                                at the end of the conference, of a joint communiqué along the
                                following lines: <list>
                                    <label>(1)</label>
                                    <item>The Allies recognize that Iran has given them every
                                        possible help, etc.</item>
                                    <label>(2)</label>
                                    <item>The independence, sovereignty and territorial integrity of
                                        Iran is confirmed, as already set forth in the Tripartite
                                        Treaty.</item>
                                    <label>(3)</label>
                                    <item>The economic needs of Iran will be considered when the
                                        peace treaty is negotiated, etc.</item>
                                </list></p>
                            <p>According to M. Soheily, Mr. <persName corresp="#p_EA1">Eden</persName> agreed to this in principle but requested that
                                the Prime Minister approach me and the Soviets to get our agreement
                                to go ahead.</p>
                            <p>Sincerely yours,</p>
                            <closer><signed><persName corresp="#p_DLGJ1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Louis
                                            G. Dreyfus, Jr.</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>